
[1]epiglottis

   EPIGLOT'TIS, n. [Gr. the tongue.] In anatomy, one of the cartilages of
   the larynx, whose use is to cover the glottis, when food or drink is
   passing into the stomach, to prevent it from entering the larynx and
   obstructing the breath.
